verbose_text: Hydrothermally stable, supported metal oxide catalysts have been used for efficient one-pot furfural synthesis by Bhaumik and Dhepe in a toluene/H 2 O biphasic system,48 similar to the one-pot method previously mentioned using H-USY zeolite.19 Improving upon 54% furfural obtained with H-USY (170 degreesC; 6 h),19 the reaction system with sol-gel-synthesized, silica supported tungsten oxide catalysts yielded 71% furfural (170 degreesC; 10 h) from isolated xylan.
